The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Jamnagar, Sept. 1 (PTI): A MiG-29 fighter aircraft crashed today in Gujarats Jamnagar when the pilot lost control during a training sortie.           
	Flight Lieutenant Dheer bailed out safely. There is no information yet about any casualty on the ground after the crash. This is the sixth IAF aircraft to crash this year.                  
	New Delhi (PTI): CPI general secretary A.B. Bardhan, who took ill while touring flood-hit Bihar, was admitted to AIIMS on Monday. The 82-year-old leader was detected with a stone in his gall bladder and doctors said they may do a surgery, party leaders said. He was flown to Delhi in the afternoon.                  
	Thrissur (PTI): A senior Catholic nun and the principal of a church-run college in Thrissur, Kerala, resigned from the order alleging mental harassment by church authorities. Sister Jesmi, a nun in the Congregation of the Mother of Carmel order has alleged she had been put under severe mental pressure, and branded a mentally disturbed person for questioning the authorities stand on several issues.                   
	 Mumbai (PTI): A senior lawyer practising in Bombay High Court died of a heart attack while arguing a case on Monday. He was in his late 80s. The high court was adjourned for about two hours following his death.                   
	 Jaipur (PTI): A youth was arrested on Sunday in connection with the murder of a woman bank employee. Dilip Kumar had allegedly murdered his former lover, Rekha, 22, when his family fixed his marriage with another woman.                   
	 Rameswaram (PTI): A college student who was swept away by a big wave at Tamil Nadus Mukunth- arayar Chattiram was rescued by marine commandos on Sunday. G. Suresh, 21, was washing clothes by the seaside when he was swept away.                                                                                                                         
